===Noun===
'''grill'''
#A [[rack]]; a [[grid]] of [[wire]] or a sheet of material with a pattern of holes or openings.
#:''There is a '''grill''' over the fan to keep fingers out.'' 
#A [[barbecue]]; a device for to suspend food above a flame to cook it.
#:''I put some peppers and mushrooms on the '''grill''' to go with dinner.''

===Verb===
'''grill'''
#To [[cook]] on a [[rack]] over a [[flame]]; to [[barbecue]].
#:''Why don't we get together Saturday and '''grill''' some burgers?''
#To [[interrogate]]; to [[question]] [[aggressively]] or [[harshly]].
#:''The polioce '''grilled''' him about whether he was involved in the crime.''